Photocatalytic activity of BFO and BNFO
The photocatalytic activity of BFO sand BLFO nanoparticles is evaluated by the
degradation of methylene blue (MB) under visible light irradiation. Herein, 0.2g sample was
mixed by 4 mg/L of MB solution at RT. The photocatalytic degradation is measured from
time unit minutes. Fig. 7 (a) shows the photo-gradation coefficients of all products vs. time.
For SGBFO and HTBFO grains, 26% and 21% of degradation take place in 300 min. However
71% and 58% of degradation take place with SGBLFO and SGBFO nanocatalysts in 5h
respectively. In principle, the efficiency of the photocatalysts depends on the factors like
crystallite size, morphology, surface area, and band gap and photoinduced electron-hole
separation efficiency of the catalyst. Fig. 7 (b) shows the rate constant of ln(C
